    "data_flow": "1) Application writes orders via normalized write model → 2) After commit, domain event is persisted to outbox table in same transaction (transactional outbox pattern) → 3) Projection Updater polls outbox (or uses CDC) and processes events → 4) Updater upserts into denormalized read projections → 5) Dashboard API queries flat projection tables with simple SELECTs. Staleness budget: seconds, not minutes — easily achievable at 500 events/day.",
    "patterns_used": [
      {
        "pattern": "CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation)",
        "rationale": "The core pattern. Separates the normalized write model (optimized for transactional integrity across 12 tables) from denormalized read projections (optimized for dashboard query patterns). Eliminates the 12-table join problem entirely on the read side."
