      "decision": "Not adopting Event Sourcing",
      "gains": "Dramatically lower complexity. The existing normalized write model is preserved — no migration needed. Team doesn't need to learn event sourcing patterns.",
      "sacrifices": "Cannot trivially replay the full event history to rebuild projections from scratch (though the outbox can be retained as a log). No time-travel queries.",
      "alternatives_considered": [
        "Full Event Sourcing — provides complete audit trail and temporal queries but is massive overengineering for a system with 500 writes/day and a working write model"
      ]
