      "DO NOT create a separate read database — single database is sufficient; splitting adds distributed consistency problems without solving a real bottleneck",
      "DO NOT try to make projections real-time consistent — eventual consistency with seconds of lag is perfectly acceptable for an operations dashboard",
      "DO NOT denormalize the write model — the 12-table normalization is correct for transactional integrity; the read projections solve the query problem",
      "DO NOT build a generic projection framework — four purpose-built projection handlers are simpler, clearer, and easier to debug than a generic engine"
