    "level": 92,
    "high_confidence_areas": [
      "CQRS is the correct pattern for this exact problem — normalized write model + analytical read queries + low write volume is the canonical CQRS use case",
      "Single-database approach is sufficient — 500 writes/day does not justify the complexity of separate databases",
      "Transactional outbox is the right synchronization mechanism at this scale",
